  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Adding a validating admission webhook targeting deployments/scale (or any other /scale) breaks all such scale operations when the dynamic webhook admission plugin attempts to serve the plugin, and convert `Deployment` to `Scale` when trying to prepare the old object.\r\n\r\nReproducer:\r\n1. register a webhook targetting `deployments/scale` (you don't need a backing hook)\r\n\r\n  <details>\r\n\r\n  <summary>whconfig.yaml</summary>\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: admissionregistration.k8s.io/v1beta1\r\nkind: ValidatingWebhookConfiguration\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: test-repro\r\nwebhooks:\r\n- name: test-repro.test.k8s.io\r\n  clientConfig:\r\n    url: https://localhost:8675/hook\r\n    caBundle: <your CA bundle>\r\n  rules:\r\n  - apiGroups: [\"*\"]\r\n    apiVersions: [\"*\"]\r\n    operations: [\"*\"]\r\n    resources: [\"deployments/scale\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\n  </details>\r\n\r\n2. `kubectl scale deploy/<some-deployment> --replicas=2`\r\n\r\n3. observe that you get an InternalServerError with an error about converting `Deployment` to `Scale`\r\n\r\nThe line responsible for the error is https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/cebb4ee2ac9e19fe90f78c3285978e585e67a3ac/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go#L177-L181\r\n\r\nKubernetes version: 8af1bf313efeeafb94c01ce04965ad8fe9cea21a and also v1.11.3",
